              <tr>
                <td colspan="5">
                  <p class="ia-table-text"><b>What is the problem under consideration? Why is government action or intervention necessary?</b></p>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">The legislation governing limited partnerships has remained largely unchanged for over 100 years. Limited partnerships remain popular business entities for a variety of legitimate purposes, for example, in venture capital. However, several high-profile cases suggest that limited partnerships have been used to facilitate criminal behaviour. The case for government intervention rests on two arguments:</p>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">• Upholding the well-established role of the state to address criminal behaviour</p>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">• Reducing information asymmetries</p>
                </td>
