          <num>89.</num>
          <content>
            <p>We expect familiarisation costs to be low. Essentially, those engaged in an LP need to know that if they are no longer active, they can contact Companies House to inform them, and if they do not, they will be struck off the register. In terms of familiarisation, this should have a negligible cost impact, especially as the strike off procedure proposed will mimic that already in existence for companies. </p>
